22/03/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Police announced on Monday (March 21st) the detention of 41 illegal migrants, including 20 children, found hidden in a truck near the town of Messolonghi.
The migrants, most of them Palestinian, Algerian and Afghans, were to enter Italy via the port of Patras.
They told police each of them paid 3,000 euros to be smuggled into Europe.
The truck driver and the driver of an escort car were detained.
(Inews, Sigmalive, Ethnos, Ennaharonline - 21/03/11)
